summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Westlake Avenue, in the City of Seattle, from Denny Way to Mercer Street, by grading and regrading the same, in accordance with Resolution No. 498 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
